author: BRAD MILNER
title: Bay Superintendent Husfelt wins Week 7 of Beat the Experts
text: Bay Superintendent Husfelt wins Week 7 of Beat the Experts Bill Husfelt of Panama City was 10-0 and only one point off a perfect tiebreaker score to win Week 7. Guest expert Guy Tunnell was 9-1. Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 12:04 PM Updated at 5:57 PM Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 12:04 PM Updated at 5:57 PM • Sign up to play our Beat the Experts football pick-em Bill Husfelt of Panama City was 10-0 and only one point off a perfect tiebreaker score to win Week 7 of The News Herald’s Beat the Experts football pick-em contest. Husfelt, Bay District Schools Superintendent and our special guest in Week 5, earned a $40 gift card to Capt. Anderson’s and a contest T-shirt. Others also finishing 10-0 and squeezed out on the tiebreaker but still earning T-shirts were: Jared Waldrip, Larry Simon, Thomas Nixon and Mel Leonard. Bay County Commission Chairman Guy Tunnell was our Week 7 guest and finished 9-1. This week’s guest is Panama City Mayor Greg Brudnicki. Online Editor Brad Milner led the experts with a 9-1 mark. Publisher Tim Thompson and Page Designer Laura Cornett were each 8-2. Executive Sports Editor Pat McCann, Assistant Sports Editor Dustin Kent and Editor Mike Cazalas were 7-3.
